OL,3,CFinance worker 'drunkenly abused'
OL,4,Ccabin crew and passengers on flight
OL,6,F"He confronted a passenger on board,
OL,7,Fand as he motioned to strike the
OL,8,Fpassenger, he struck a cabin crew
OL,9,Fworker who tried to intervene. The
OL,10,Fcabin crew worker had to take a
OL,11,Fsignificant period off work to
OL,12,Frecover."
OL,14,FDet Sgt Ian Warncken, from Gatwick
OL,15,FCID, said: "This case demonstrates the
OL,16,Fimpact alcohol can have on your body.
OL,17,FThe impact increases when you are in
OL,18,Fthe air, flying at a higher altitude
OL,19,Fand with a reduced air pressure.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
